ENQUIRE ABOUT SCHOLARSHIPS

US GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS

These are awards offered by the government to encourage students to study in the US. It includes the Fulbright Foreign Students Program and the Hubert Humphrey Fellowship Program.

NON-GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS

Offered by various different trusts, foundations, and organizations to students pursuing a specific course stream to encourage participation and development in the said field.

INSTITUTIONAL SCHOLARSHIPS

Offered by universities in the US  to students who are pursuing education with them.

SCHOLARSHIPS

KNOW MORE

STUDENT MINIMUM WAGE

7.25 USD/hour

Students can expect to earn a minimum of 7.25 USD/hour during their first 90 consecutive calendar days of employment with an employer.

PART TIME JOBS IN US

20 hours a week

Students holding an F-1 visa can work up to 20 hours per week while school is in session. They can wrk full-time during the periods when school is not in session or during the annual vacation.

WORK PERMIT AFTER STUDY IN US

2 years + 1 year for OPT

PGWP is usually issued for the length of the study program. The maximum length of the post work permit is two years and an additional year for Optional Practical Training.
